in in effect. The President addresses the National Assembly, can send messages to it, and recommend financial measures. The President also submits appointments and measures to the National Assembly for approval and ratification. Overall, the National Assembly and the President work collaboratively in the legislative and executive functions of the Zambian government, with checks and balances in place to ensure accountability and governance.", "input": "\nYou are a helpful assistant responsible for generating a comprehensive summary of the data provided below.\nGiven one or two entities, and a list of descriptions, all related to the same entity or group of entities.\nPlease concatenate all of these into a single, comprehensive description. Make sure to include information collected from all the descriptions.\nIf the provided descriptions are contradictory, please resolve the contradictions and provide a single, coherent summary.\nMake sure it is written in third person, and include the entity names so we have the full context.\n\n#######\n-Data-\nEntities: [\"NATIONAL ASSEMBLY\", \"PRESIDENT\"]\nDescription List: [\"The National Assembly approves international agreements and treaties negotiated by the President\", \"The National Assembly can pass resolutions affecting the President's ability to perform executive functions\", \"The National Assembly can resolve that the President has committed violations and should cease to hold office\", \"The National Assembly can verify the Chief Justice's certificate regarding the President's incapacityThe President has the power to dissolve the National Assembly\", \"The National Assembly debates and votes on motions regarding allegations against the President\", \"The National Assembly debates motions regarding the President's capacity and potential removal\", \"The National Assembly has the authority to remove the President's immunity from criminal proceedings based on a report submitted by the President\", \"The National Assem